article.headline: Chicago St. 89, W. New Mexico 79
article.story: LAS CRUCES, N.M. (AP) -- David Holston scored 26 points, all but two coming on 3-point shots, as Chicago State beat Western New Mexico 89-79 in Saturday night's second round of the Lou Henson Classic. Holston was 8-of-19 behind the 3-point arc. His 3-pointer opened the game's scoring and he had nine points in the first half to give the Cougars (3-6) a 43-30 halftime lead. JJ Galberth scored 27 points for Western New Mexico (3-6). Kris Taylor grabbed seven rebounds for the Mustangs. Both teams lost in the tourney's first round Friday. Western New Mexico lost 84-82 to North Texas and Chicago State lost 94-61 to New Mexico State.
